T1  - Endometrial intraepithelial neoplasia.
DO  - https://dx.doi.org/10.5858/arpa.2012-0709-RA
A1  - Owings, Richard A
A1  - Quick, Charles M
Y1  - 2014//
N2  - CONTEXT: Developed in conjunction with molecular and progression data, the sequence classification schema for endometrial intraepithelial neoplasia (EIN)/benign hyperplasia (BH) provides an easy to adopt and reproducible method for classification of endometrial biopsies., OBJECTIVE: To review current data supporting the use of BH/EIN to classify endometrial biopsies, and to discuss the hormone-driven endometrial sequence from anovulation/disordered proliferative endometrium through BH and EIN and their diagnostic difficulty., DATA SOURCES: A comprehensive review of EIN literature based on literature indexed by PubMed (National Library of Medicine) and Google Scholar., CONCLUSIONS: The BH/EIN schema is gaining wider acceptance among pathologist and clinicians. The research leading to the EIN criteria is based on molecular and progression data. The BH/EIN schema has better reproducibility among pathologists, is intuitively easy to use, and requires understanding of endometrial physiology and neoplasia.
