T1  - Lower expression of ER-alpha36 is associated with the development of endometrial hyperplasia in PCOS patients.
DO  - https://dx.doi.org/10.14670/HH-28.1491
A1  - Lin, Sheng-Li
A1  - Tu, Bin-Bin
A1  - Du, Xiao-Guo
A1  - Yan, Li-Ying
A1  - Qiao, Jie
Y1  - 2013//
Y2  - 20130521//
N2  - OBJECTIVE: To explore the expression change of ER-alpha36 in endometria of PCOS patients., METHODS: Proliferative endometria were collected and divided into three groups: CE group (n=30), proliferative endometria from control women; PCOSE group (n=30), proliferative endometria from PCOS patients; HPCOSE group (n=15), hyperplastic endometria from PCOS patients. The cellular localization of ER-alpha36 and ER-alpha66 was analyzed by immunohistochemistry, and expression of ER-alpha36 and ER-alpha66 was determined by immunohistochemistry and Real-Time Quantitative PCR. The correlation between serum hormone concentration and expression of ER-alpha36 and ER-alpha66 was analyzed., RESULTS: ER-alpha36 was localized on the cell surface, cytoplasm and nucleus of glandular epithelial cells of both CE and PCOSE groups, mainly on the cell surface, and ER-alpha66 was localized on the nucleus. The protein and mRNA expression of ER-alpha36 was decreased from CE, PCOSE to HPCOSE group, while expression of ER-alpha66 showed no obvious difference among groups. The expression ratio of ER-alpha36 to ER-alpha66 of CE, PCOSE and HPCOSE group showed a decreasing tendency. The expression of ER-alpha36 and its expressive ratio to ER-alpha66 was negatively correlated with serum concentration of LH, LH/FSH, testosterone and androstenedione., CONCLUSIONS: Lower expression of ER-alpha66 is associated with the development of endometrial hyperplasia in PCOS patients.
